<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1306,2012]" box="[151,255,1306,1332]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1306,2012]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">
The classification of 
<taxonomicName box="[448,702,1346,1371]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatum">
<emphasis box="[448,702,1346,1371]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium papillatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been a matter of considerable debate. In 
<number box="[1239,1298,1346,1372]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1886.0">1886</number>
Ridley and Dendy established a new species 
<taxonomicName box="[549,787,1386,1411]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="caminatus">
<emphasis box="[549,787,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Suberites caminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A year latter they erected a new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1887" authorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" authorityYear="1887" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="microstomus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. microstomus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley" box="[206,475,1426,1452]" pageId="23" pageNumber="134" refString="Ridley, S. O. &amp; Dendy, A. (1887) Report on the Monaxonida collected by H. M. S. &quot; Challenger &quot; during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. &quot; Challenger &quot;, 1873 - 1876, Zoology 20 (59), 1 - 275." type="journal article" year="1887">
Ridley &amp; Dendy, 
<number box="[414,475,1426,1452]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1887.0">1887</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, out of one 
<typeStatus box="[616,707,1426,1452]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[747,898,1426,1451]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="caminatus">
<emphasis box="[747,898,1426,1451]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. caminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkpatrick" box="[913,1134,1426,1452]" pageId="23" pageNumber="134" refString="Kirkpatrick, R. (1908) Porifera (Sponges). II. Tetraxonida, Dendy. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1908">
Kirkpatrick (
<number box="[1064,1125,1426,1452]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
established new varieties for the species of Ridley and Dendy, 
<taxonomicName box="[604,937,1466,1491]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="variety" species="caminatus" variety="papillatus">
<emphasis box="[604,937,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. caminatus var. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing from the typical morphs by the locality of ostia exclusively on the tops of small surface raisings and 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1325,1506,1531]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="variety" species="microstomus" variety="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[985,1325,1506,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. microstomus var. stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing from the typical morphs by the stellate shape of the surface ostial areas and by the thicker and denser cortical tylostyles. 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent" box="[278,456,1586,1612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="135" refString="Topsent, E. (1917) Spongiaires. In: Joubin, L. (Ed.), Deuxieme Expedition Antarctique Francaise (1908 - 1910) Commandee par le Dr. Jean Charcot. Sciences Physiques: Documents Scientifiques, 4. Masson &amp; Cie, Paris, pp. 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="1917">
Topsent (
<number box="[386,447,1586,1612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1917.0">1917</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
raised the variety 
<taxonomicName box="[672,789,1586,1611]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis box="[672,789,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species level and placed it in 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1290,1586,1611]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1290,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">T. papillatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton" box="[236,405,1626,1652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="133" refString="Burton, M. (1929) Porifera. Part II. Antarctic sponges. British Antarctic (&quot; Terra Nova &quot;) Expedition, 1910. Natural History Report, Zoology, 6 (4), 393 - 458." type="journal article" year="1929">
Burton (
<number box="[336,397,1626,1652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
agreed with validity of this species but kept it in 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1133,1626,1651]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1024,1133,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Suberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[1186,1336,1626,1651]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1336,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" pageId="23" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. Part 1. Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E. P., Andriyashev, A. P. &amp; Ushakov, P. V. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958), Explorations of the fauna of the seas. Vol. 2 (10). Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, 6 - 133, 443 - 448." type="journal article" year="1964">
Koltun (
<number box="[159,220,1666,1692]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[400,546,1666,1691]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis box="[400,546,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[613,763,1666,1691]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="caminatus">
<emphasis box="[613,763,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. caminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[820,998,1666,1691]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="microstomus">
<emphasis box="[820,998,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. microstomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and gave the name of the senior synonym, 
<taxonomicName box="[237,391,1706,1731]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="caminatus">
<emphasis box="[237,391,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. caminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Llater he transferred 
<taxonomicName box="[671,791,1706,1731]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="caminatus">
<emphasis box="[671,791,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">caminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[838,957,1706,1731]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,957,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any comments (
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" box="[1265,1423,1706,1732]" pageId="23" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1976) Porifera. Part I: Antarctic sponges. B. A. N. Z. Antarctic Research Expedition 1929 - 1931 Reports, Ser. B (Zoology and Botany), 9 (4), 147 - 198." type="journal article" year="1976">
Koltun 
<number box="[1360,1423,1706,1732]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Boury­Esnault and van 
<bibRefCitation author="Beveren" box="[434,618,1746,1772]" pageId="23" pageNumber="133" refString="Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; van Beveren, M. (1982) Les Demosponges du plateau continental de Kerguelen-Heard. Comite national francais des recherches antarctiques, 52, 1 - 175." type="journal article" year="1982">
Beveren (
<number box="[549,610,1746,1772]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
advocated the validity of 
<taxonomicName box="[933,1113,1746,1771]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="microstomus">
<emphasis box="[933,1113,1746,1771]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">S. microstomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and also followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent" pageId="23" pageNumber="135" refString="Topsent, E. (1917) Spongiaires. In: Joubin, L. (Ed.), Deuxieme Expedition Antarctique Francaise (1908 - 1910) Commandee par le Dr. Jean Charcot. Sciences Physiques: Documents Scientifiques, 4. Masson &amp; Cie, Paris, pp. 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="1917">
Topsent (
<number box="[159,222,1786,1812]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="1917.0">1917</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, maintaining 
<taxonomicName box="[391,508,1786,1811]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis box="[391,508,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[546,665,1786,1811]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,665,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1306,2012]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1435,152,218]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">
Herein, we follow Topsent and Boury­Esnault &amp; van Beveren considering 
<taxonomicName box="[1092,1219,1826,1851]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatum">
<emphasis box="[1092,1219,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">papillatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a valid species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,268,1866,1891]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; its regular radial skeleton and presence of papillae do not correspond with the accepted definition of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,292,1906,1931]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,292,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Suberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see van 
<bibRefCitation author="Soest" box="[405,541,1906,1932]" pageId="23" pageNumber="135" refString="Soest, R. W. M. van (2002) Family Suberitidae Schmidt, 1870. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera. A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 227 - 244." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Soest 
<number box="[477,541,1906,1932]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, the location of exhalant papillae and ostia exclusively on the upper surface, the single­layered cortex and only two tylostyle categories are typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[1184,1303,1946,1971]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1184,1303,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">Tentorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName box="[213,372,1986,2011]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatum">
<emphasis box="[213,372,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">T. papillatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considerably differs from the 
<typeStatus box="[744,795,1986,2012]" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<emphasis box="[907,1106,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName box="[907,1101,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Thecophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semisuberites">T. semisuberites</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and also from the recently described 
<taxonomicName authority="Ilan, Gugel, Galil &amp; Janussen, 2003" authorityName="Ilan, Gugel, Galil &amp; Janussen" authorityYear="2003" box="[271,865,152,178]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="levantinum">
<emphasis box="[271,431,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">T. levantinum</emphasis>
Ilan, Gugel, Galil &amp; Janussen, 
<quantity box="[806,865,152,178]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking a dense, solid, lateral sheath made of principal spicules placed longitudinally. Thus, the taxonomic position of 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1162,192,217]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Tentorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="papillatum">
<emphasis box="[1006,1162,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">T. papillatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain.
</paragraph>
